page.title: 20MARSHES.
page.content: In the West of our Domesday square most of it is taken up by marshes.At the moment farms have drained the land and cattle are grazing.We went to Ivy farm where we saw owls,brown and white.We had to be very quiet.We also went to Sprats Water Nature Reserve.Here are lots of birds.There are a lot of Holiday makers who come to Oulton Broad every year and go up the Broads on boats.Near the Waveney Inn is a marina.Here is where most of the boats stop.There are also a couple of other farms .One of the other farms is called Beech Farm.There are also quite a few more.There is a mill called the Share Mill.This mill does not work any more.
